# Cave Runtime — code owners
#
# https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-security/about-codeowners
#
# Anyone in a section's owner list is auto-requested for review on PRs
# that touch matching paths. Later entries override earlier ones.
#
# Until a co-maintainer joins, @LordGnomish is the single owner of
# everything. Sub-area rules are intentionally explicit so the file
# doubles as a map of who-cares-about-what once the team grows.

# Default — every path.
* @LordGnomish

# CI / GitHub config — review carefully, can break the whole repo.
/.github/                @LordGnomish
/.github/workflows/      @LordGnomish
/.github/CODEOWNERS      @LordGnomish

# Charter & ADRs — governance documents, immutable history.
/docs/charter*           @LordGnomish
/docs/adr/               @LordGnomish

# Parity & compliance scaffolding — touched by automation, but humans
# review the schema. (Crates moved to themed subdirs in 9c15b3fb;
# patterns below use the post-reorg paths.)
/crates/ops/cave-upstream/         @LordGnomish
/crates/ops/cave-upstream-watchd/  @LordGnomish
/docs/parity/                       @LordGnomish
/scripts/build-parity-index.py      @LordGnomish

# Security-sensitive crates — extra scrutiny.
/crates/security/cave-vault/     @LordGnomish
/crates/security/cave-identity/  @LordGnomish
/crates/security/cave-policy/    @LordGnomish
/crates/security/cave-sign/      @LordGnomish
/crates/security/cave-trivy/     @LordGnomish

# Licensing & legal headers — every .rs file enforces SPDX via CI.
LICENSE                  @LordGnomish
deny.toml                @LordGnomish
/scripts/check-spdx.sh   @LordGnomish
